<h3 id="why-to-ask-good-questions">Why To Ask Good Questions?</h3>

<p>Iâ€™ll dive right in and say a few words about why I think this is absolutely crucial to ask good questions. It turns out that people ask questions when they need something. So a useful answer is usually what they hope for. However, does really anybody feel like helping other people when they pose a stupid, broad, vague etc. question? I donâ€™t think so! Such questions tend to be avoided, answered in a similar manner, handed to somebody else or, at best, people who ask such dumb questions get, instead of an answer, a question in return. Any of these waste time and nothing gets solved.</p>

